protocol_name: Protein extraction, alkylation, and digestion for LC/MS of HEK-293
protocol_name_html: Protein extraction, alkylation, and digestion for LC/MS of HEK-293
description: Protocol for protein extraction, alkylation, and digestion to obtain LC/MS (liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry) data of calculated protein signal intensities in HEK-293 cells to monitor them.
before_start:
Prepare a Krebs-Ringer-Buffer: 

  • 154 mM NaCl
  • 5.6 mM KCl
  • 5.5 mM glucose
  • 20.1 mM HEPES pH 7.4
  • 25 mM NaHCO3

components.data: Extract the HEK-293 proteins using the standard protocol for the RIPA buffer (NACALAI, INC., Kyoto, Japan).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Extract the HEK-293 proteins using the standard protocol for the RIPA buffer (NACALAI, INC., Kyoto, Japan).

components.data: Wash approximately 106 harvested cells once in Krebs-Ringer-Buffer (KRB; 154 mM NaCl, 5.6 mM KCl, 5.5 mM glucose, 20.1 mM HEPES pH 7.4, 25 mM NaHCO3).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Wash approximately 106 harvested cells once in Krebs-Ringer-Buffer (KRB; 154 mM NaCl, 5.6 mM KCl, 5.5 mM glucose, 20.1 mM HEPES pH 7.4, 25 mM NaHCO3).

components.data: Resuspend the cells in 30 µl of RIPA buffer, passed in and out through 21G needles for destruction, and incubate on ice for 1 h.
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Resuspend the cells in 30 µl of RIPA buffer, passed in and out through 21G needles for destruction, and incubate on ice for 1 h.

components.data: Centrifuge the cells at 10,000 g for 10 min at 4°C.
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Centrifuge the cells at 10,000 g for 10 min at 4°C.
Collect the supernatants.

components.data: Quantify the proteins by using a Micro BCA Protein Assay Kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, U.S.A.).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Quantify the proteins by using a Micro BCA Protein Assay Kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, U.S.A.).

components.data: Solidify the samples in acrylamide gel. For further steps, use XL-Tryp Kit Direct Digestion (APRO SCIENCE, Naruto, Japan).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Solidify the samples in acrylamide gel. For further steps, use XL-Tryp Kit Direct Digestion (APRO SCIENCE, Naruto, Japan).
Wash the samples in ultrapure water. (1/2)
Wash the samples in ultrapure water. (2/2)
Wash the samples in dehydration solution. (1/3)
Wash the samples in dehydration solution. (2/3)
Wash the samples in dehydration solution. (3/3)
Dry the samples.

components.data: Process the samples using an In-Gel R-CAM Kit (APRO SCIENCE, Naruto, Japan).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Process the samples using an In-Gel R-CAM Kit (APRO SCIENCE, Naruto, Japan).
Reduce the samples for 2 h at 37°C.

components.data: Alkylate the samples for 30 min at room temperature.
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Alkylate the samples for 30 min at room temperature.
Wash samples with ultrapure water. (1/5)
Wash samples with ultrapure water. (2/5)
Wash samples with ultrapure water. (3/5)
Wash samples with ultrapure water. (4/5)
Wash samples with ultrapure water. (5/5)
Wash samples with destaining solution. (1/2)
Wash samples with destaining solution. (2/2)
Dry the samples.
Trypsinize the resultant samples overnight at 35°C.

components.data: Collect the dissolved digested peptides by ZipTipC18 (Merck Millipore,Corp., Billerica, U.S.A.).
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Collect the dissolved digested peptides by ZipTipC18 (Merck Millipore,Corp., Billerica, U.S.A.).

components.data: Dampen the tips with acetonitrile x three tips. (1/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Dampen the tips with acetonitrile x three tips. (1/2)

components.data: Dampen the tips with acetonitrile x three tips. (2/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Dampen the tips with acetonitrile x three tips. (2/2)

components.data: Equilibrate tips with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (1/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Equilibrate tips with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (1/2)

components.data: Equilibrate tips with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (2/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Equilibrate tips with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (2/2)

components.data: Collect the peptides by ~20 cycles of aspiration and dispensing x three tips.
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Collect the peptides by ~20 cycles of aspiration and dispensing x three tips.

components.data: Wash the peptides with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acidx three tips. (1/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Wash the peptides with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acidx three tips. (1/2)

components.data: Wash the peptides with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (2/2)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Wash the peptides with 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid x three tips. (2/2)

components.data: Elute by 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid /50% acetonitrile with aspiration and dispense x three tips. (1/5)
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Elute by 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid /50% acetonitrile with aspiration and dispense x three tips. (1/5)

components.name: Description

components.name: Description

source_data.description: Elute by 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid /50% acetonitrile with aspiration and dispense x three tips. (3/5)

components.name: Description

source_data.description: Elute by 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid /50% acetonitrile with aspiration and dispense x three tips. (4/5)

components.name: Description

source_data.description: Elute by 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid /50% acetonitrile with aspiration and dispense x three tips. (5/5)
Vacuum dry the peptides.
Store the finalized samples at −20°C.

components.data: Before performing LC/MS, resuspend samples in 0.1% formic acid.
components.name: Description

source_data.description: Before performing LC/MS, resuspend samples in 0.1% formic acid.

components.data: Quantify the amounts with the Pierce Quantitative Colorimetric Peptide Assay (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, U.S.A.).
